cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with object detection and action recognition in aerial images using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of object detection and tracking algorithms in aerial images could also place the paper in cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to associate high-resolution aerial imagery with pedestrian action labels, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
